olive oil
1 packet pine nuts
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 ciabatta
1 cucumber
2 tomato
1 bag Mixed Leaves
2 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 bag herbs
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Heat a frying pan over medium-high
heat
• Toast pine nuts, tossing, until
golden, 3-4 mins. Transfer to a bowl
• In a separate bowl, combine pork,
seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil
• Return frying pan to medium-high
heat with a drizzle of oil. Cook pork,
until cooked through, 3-4 mins
each side

• Slice ciabatta in half. Toast or grill
to your liking, then tear into chunks
• Roughly chop cucumber
and tomato

• In a large bowl, combine cucumber,
tomato, ciabatta croutons, mixed
leaves and balsamic dressing.
Season
• Slice pork
• Plate up salad and pork and top
with creamy pesto
• Sprinkle with Parmesan and pine
nuts. Tear over herbs to serve